interclusam, ‘ closed against me,’ keeps up the metaphor of a ‘course ’ (curriculum) which had to be cleared. In signum . . . sustulisti there is a change to a military metaphor. A red or white flag (properly vexillum), hung out from the general’s tent, was the signal for marching out to battle, or to the founding of a colony; for the former cp.
